
Apertium (rule-based machine translation) 2007-Present
Maintained and expanded a number of translators, including English-Spanish and English-Catalan
Created a number of new translators, including Spanish-Aragonese and Basque-English
Enhancements to the translation engine (C++)
Enhancements to the dictionary management tools (Java)
Added Unicode support to a number of tools, including apertium-transfer-tools (statistical rule induction) (C++)
Wrote a number of scripts and tools (Bourne shell, Perl)
Member of Project Management Committee (2010-2014)
Mentor for Google Summer of Code (2009-2014)
Mentor for Google Code-In (2010-2014)

DBpedia Extraction Framework 2011-Present
Localisation (Scala: adapting the framework to a number of languages, including Polish, Irish, and Catalan.)

Tesseract OCR (https://code.google.com/p/tesseract-ocr) 2009-2010
Release engineering (C++: portability, build, documentation)


